The paper discusses a new type of artificial neuron for use in deep learning models, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the improved accuracy of the new neuron compared to standard ones, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments conducted in the paper involve image classification tasks, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the inspiration for deep learning models from biological nervous systems, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of the new neuron in feed-forward and convolutional neural networks, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
